entry.def: Superannuation is money which people pay regularly into a special fund so that when they retire from their job they will receive money regularly as a pension.

example.ex: The union pressed for a superannuation scheme.
example.tran: 工会敦促制定一个退休金方案。

means.word_mean: 1. a monthly payment made to someone who is retired from work
2. the property of being out of date and not current
3. the act of discharging someone because of age (especially to cause someone to retire from service on a pension)
